class Solution:
    def hasAlternatingBits(self, n: int) -> bool:
        x = n ^ (n >> 1)
        return (x & (x + 1)) == 0


"""
Approach & Reasoning:

If a number has alternating bits (e.g., 101010...),
then shifting it right by 1 and XORing with itself
produces a sequence of all 1s.

Example:
n = 5 (101)
n >> 1 = 010
n ^ (n >> 1) = 111

So for alternating bits:
    x = n ^ (n >> 1)
    x must be of the form 111... (all 1s)

A number with all 1s satisfies:
    x & (x + 1) == 0

Therefore:
1) Compute x = n ^ (n >> 1)
2) Check if x is all 1s using (x & (x + 1)) == 0

Time Complexity: O(1)
Space Complexity: O(1)
"""
